 style=3D"clear:both"></div><p>If you know how many gallons you are using, =
but need to express the volume in acre-feet (AF) or, in rare cases, cubic f=
eet (CF), &nbsp;just plug in the information below and you=E2=80=99re set.<=
/p>
<h2>Values used in the calculator.</h2>
<ul>
<li>1 AF =3D 325,851 gallons</li>
<li>1 AF =3D 43,560 cubic feet</li>
<li>1 CF =3D 7.48 gallon</li>
</ul>
<p>The exact number of gallons per acre-foot equals 325,851.385 gallons. Ge=
nerally, most people calculate the conversion without the decimal. 325,851 =
is the base used in the calculator below.</p>
<h2>How to use the calculator.</h2>
<ol>
<li>Enter the number of gallons you wish to convert in the top of the form.=
 DO NOT USE COMMAS.</li>
<li>Select acre-feet or cubic feet.</li>
<li>Click =E2=80=9CCalculate. The converted expression will appear in the l=
ast box (conversion). If you selected acre-feet, the converted figure is an=
 expression in acre-feet. To recalculate with a different expression (for e=
xample, cubic feet instead of acre-feet), be sure to select cubic feet in t=
he drop down menu, and click the calculate button again so that the math wi=
ll reset.</li>
</ol>
<p>To test the calculator, experiment using 325851 gallons. The result will=
 be 1 acre-foot, which will match the formula above.</p>
